37560>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
37560>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
37560>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
37563>>>
37563>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
37563>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
37563>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
37563>>>        Case Begin
37563>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
37565>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
37565>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
37565>>>                Case Break
37566>>>                
37566>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
37569>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
37569>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
37569>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
37569>>>                Case Break
37570>>>                
37570>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
37573>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
37573>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
37573>>>                Case Break
37574>>>                
37574>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
37574>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
37574>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
37574>>>                  
37574>>>        Case End
37574>>>
37574>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
37574>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
37574>>>        Send SetActionButtons
37575>>>
37575>>>    End_Procedure
37576>>>
37576>>>End_Object
